  "title" : "How can I set the EOM byte in JMeter?",
  "body" : "<p>I am load testing a <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transmission_Control_Protocol\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">TCP</a> server in JMeter in GUI mode and am getting this error:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/Wr77K.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/Wr77K.png\" alt=\"Enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n<p>I read about adding the end of line byte, but my data kind of has two bytes as the ending message byte = &quot;0d0a&quot;.</p>\n<p>How can I use BinaryTCPClientImpl class and set this EOM byte?</p>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>I have always used the GUI mode. Do I have to extend the BinaryTCPClientImpl class to set the EOM byte?</li>\n</ol>\n"
